  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>RE-CONCTRACT TENDER</p><ol><li>Source for tender of notice and attend site show round.</li><li>Know the nature of tender and allocation of work before collecting of tender documents.</li><li>Assist in taking off quantities and Bills of Quantities.</li><li>Check quotation received according to specification requirement.</li><li>Prepare cost comparison to management and submit for approval.</li><li>Assist in the identification and engagement of good subcontractors / suppliers.</li><li>Compilation of suppliers and subcontractors list with grading.</li><li>Discuss with the management for the submission of tender at a date of fixed by the contracts manager / managing director before the closing date of tender (i.e. 4 days prior to tender closing date).</li></ol><p>POST-CONTRACT ADMINISTRATION</p><ol><li>Verify and source for sub-contractors / suppliers and materials.</li><li>Prepare letter of award.</li><li>Attend site meeting (if required).</li><li>Prepare monthly project progress claim.</li><li>Check with site personnel and prepare variation order claim on monthly basis.</li><li>Prepare and verify sub-contractors / suppliers progress claim.</li><li>Attend to dispute arises due to claim & variation order on monthly basis.</li><li>Ensure subcontractors & suppliers are awarded timely without jeopardizing the progress of work.</li><li>Costs control between budget & expenditure.</li><li>Control of overall project costs to ensure expenditure is 10% below budget.</li></ol><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ol><li>Bachelor's degree in Quantity Surveying or equivalent.</li><li>Entry level candidates are welcomed to apply. </li><li>Good communication skill, meticulous and attentive.</li><li>Able to work both independently and as a team.</li><li>Willing to travel to various project site for site meeting as and when required.</li></ol><p><strong>Others information:</strong></p><ol><li>Work location at Wood Square Tower 1.</li><li>5 days’ work week.</li></ol>",
